name: Spaghetti Carbonara
ingredients: Salt and freshly ground black pepper
recipes: Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.
In a large skillet, cook pancetta or bacon over medium heat until crispy. Add garlic and cook until fragrant.
In a bowl, whisk together eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Drain spaghetti and add to the skillet with pancetta/bacon. Remove from heat and let cool for a minute or two.
Add egg mixture to skillet and toss until spaghetti is coated. Add parsley and season with salt and pepper to taste.
details: Spaghetti carbonara is a classic Italian dish that features a creamy sauce made with eggs and Parmesan cheese. The dish is typically served with crispy pancetta or bacon and fresh parsley.

name: Chicken Alfredo
ingredients: 1 pound chicken breast, cut into bite-sized pieces
Salt and freshly ground black pepper
recipes: Cook fettuccine according to package instructions.
In a large skillet, cook chicken over medium-high heat until browned and cooked through. Add garlic and cook until fragrant.
Add butter to skillet and let melt. Add heavy cream and stir to combine.

Drain fettuccine and add to skillet with chicken and sauce. Toss until well coated. Garnish with chopped parsley.
